About Robert W. Lazar
Bob is one of the most well respected business professionals in the Capital Region. After a long career as the president of the New York Business Development Corporation, Bob became the Director of Business Development at TBC in 2010. In this role, he is involved with strategic planning, client advisory services and business development.A little known fact, 30 years prior to taking the position, Bob had taken a sabbatical from his position in banking to obtain the experience needed to earn his CPA license. He earned that experience right here at Teal, Becker & Chiaramonte. In addition to his role at TBC, Bob is a board member for Sterling Bank Corp, parent company of Sterling National Bank, a NYSE company with over $7 billion in assets where he also serves on the audit and compensation committees.

Community involvement

Living Resources, Board Member, Vice President
NYBDC Charitable Foundation, Chairman
St. Peter’s Hospital Foundation, Chair Leadership Campaign, Executive and Endowment Committee
Teresian House, Audit and Finance Committee Member
Union College, Executive Committee Member
University at Albany School of Business Advisory Board, Chairman
NYBDC Board Member
Capital Region Sponsor-A-Scholar Board Member

 
Just for fun

When Bob first worked for TBC in 1981, he sat next to Katie Doran and John Teevan who were staff accountants at the time.
Bob enjoys being with his family, including his eight grandchildren, and spending time at his home in Bolton Landing. He is also likely to be found with his friends, either running, playing golf, travelling, boating, or playing water sports.

 






  Professional Credentials

Licensed Certified Public Accountant (CPA)


